drug.name: Valinomycin
drug.description: A cyclododecadepsipeptide ionophore antibiotic produced by Streptomyces fulvissimus and related to the enniatins. It is composed of 3 moles each of L-valine, D-alpha-hydroxyisovaleric acid, D-valine, and L-lactic acid linked alternately to form a 36-membered ring. (From Merck Index, 11th ed) Valinomycin is a potassium selective ionophore and is commonly used as a tool in biochemical studies.

article.citation: Pinkerton M, Steinrauf LK, Dawkins P: The molecular structure and some transport properties of valinomycin. Biochem Biophys Res Commun. 1969 May 22;35(4):512-8.
